cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on deep learning for vision tasks, specifically human pose estimation, and evaluates the performance of convolutional neural networks with a linear regression top layer. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the stochastic nature of optimization methods, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a systematic evaluation and statistical analysis of deep regression techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep networks also suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of deep regression on three vision problems, which could also fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
